fake_twitter

Preparations

    0. Install following modules
        * AnyEvent
        * AnyEvent::Twitter
        * Tatsumaki
        * URI
        * JSON
        * Perl6::Slurp
        * Data::Validate::URI
        * Plack
        * Plack::Session::Store::File
        * Text::Xslate
        * Web::Scraper

    1. Create a 'oauth.json' file using http://cpansearch.perl.org/src/PUNYTAN/AnyEvent-Twitter-0.51/eg/gen_token.pl

    2. $ touch '{}' > filter.json

    3. $ mkdir log session

    4. $ echo 'YourLoginPassPhrase' > phrase

Usage

    1. $ plackup kvs.psgi 

    2. $ perl chirp.pl

    3. $ plackup -p 3000 front.psgi

    4. $ tail -f chirp.log
        This enables you to peep at real time tweet log.

Note

    * Do not expose the port 5000 to the outside of your local network because there is no verification transaction.

    * I use nginx to enable reverse proxy.

    * I use daemontools for logging and watching process.

